                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/393c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 22, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. The Bolivian Minister has informed me that Bolivia holds one Paraguayan
                    officer and twelve soldiers prisoners, who are all at Villa Montes. The Bolivian
                    Government proposes the immediate exchange of all Paraguayan prisoners held by
                    Bolivia for all Bolivian prisoners held by Paraguay. Please communicate this
                    proposal to Paraguayan authorities, and informally urge that the exchange be
                    consummated without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
